---
import CaseStudyLayout from '../../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro';
import CaseStudyRow from '../../components/case-studies/CaseStudyRow.astro';
import CaseStudyImageColumn from '../../components/case-studies/CaseStudyImageColumn.astro';
import CaseStudyTextColumn from '../../components/case-studies/CaseStudyTextColumn.astro';
import CaseStudyWideImage from '../../components/case-studies/CaseStudyWideImage.astro';
import CaseStudyQuote from '../../components/case-studies/CaseStudyQuote.astro';
import { getCaseStudyBySlug } from '../../data/caseStudies';

const study = getCaseStudyBySlug('bravo-farms');

if (!study) {
  throw new Error('Missing Bravo Farms case study metadata.');
}
---

<CaseStudyLayout
  slug={study.slug}
  title={study.title}
  description="A closer look at the Bravo Farms ecommerce redesign and Shopify experience."
  summary="A redesign focused on bringing Bravo Farms&apos; destination energy, product variety, and gift-shop personality into a clearer ecommerce experience."
  services={study.services}
  client="Bravo Farms"
  heroImage={study.cardImage}
  heroAlt={study.cardAlt}
>
  <CaseStudyRow>
    <CaseStudyImageColumn
      src={study.cardImage}
      alt={study.cardAlt}
      caption="Early homepage direction and merchandising mockups."
    />
    <CaseStudyTextColumn>
      <h2>Client Overview</h2>
      <p>
        Bravo Farms is a destination business known for gifts, food products,
        roadside stops, and a playful visual identity. The challenge was to
        present that breadth in a way that felt intentional online rather than
        crowded or disconnected.
      </p>
      <h3>Project Goals</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Clarify the customer journey from discovery to product browsing.</li>
        <li>Translate the in-person brand character into ecommerce visuals.</li>
        <li>Organize merchandising so featured collections felt easier to explore.</li>
      </ul>
    </CaseStudyTextColumn>
  </CaseStudyRow>

  <CaseStudyWideImage
    src={study.cardImage}
    alt={study.cardAlt}
    caption="Product-forward layouts used to reinforce the brand&apos;s colorful, giftable personality."
  />

  <CaseStudyRow>
    <CaseStudyTextColumn>
      <h2>Challenges</h2>
      <p>
        The site needed to balance a lot of visual energy with a cleaner
        shopping experience. Messaging, browsing paths, and merchandising all
        had to feel more deliberate without losing the warmth of the brand.
      </p>
      <h3>Solutions</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Introduced stronger visual hierarchy for homepage and collections.</li>
        <li>Used larger product imagery to make featured categories easier to scan.</li>
        <li>Created more consistent spacing and grouping across promotional content.</li>
      </ul>
    </CaseStudyTextColumn>
    <CaseStudyImageColumn
      src={study.cardImage}
      alt={study.cardAlt}
      caption="Collection and merchandising presentation with a cleaner browsing rhythm."
    />
  </CaseStudyRow>

  <CaseStudyQuote author="Bravo Farms engagement">
    The redesign direction focused on making the experience feel more curated
    and easier to browse while preserving the brand&apos;s playful, destination-led
    character.
  </CaseStudyQuote>

  <CaseStudyRow>
    <CaseStudyImageColumn
      src={study.cardImage}
      alt={study.cardAlt}
      caption="The revised interface emphasized product discovery and stronger page rhythm."
    />
    <CaseStudyTextColumn>
      <h2>Results</h2>
      <p>
        The resulting design concept brought more structure to the shopping
        experience and gave Bravo Farms a more polished visual system for
        digital storytelling.
      </p>
      <h3>Summary</h3>
      <p>
        This case study establishes the template for future RedTail case-study
        pages: clear narrative framing, strong visual presentation, and enough
        flexibility to expand with additional screenshots and refined copy.
      </p>
    </CaseStudyTextColumn>
  </CaseStudyRow>
</CaseStudyLayout>
